# Architecture principles

Conventions established by [docs/architecture-refactor.md](docs/architecture-refactor.md). Complements [.cursor/rules/project-context.mdc](.cursor/rules/project-context.mdc) and [.cursor/rules/no-backward-compatibility.mdc](.cursor/rules/no-backward-compatibility.mdc).

## Principles

- **Single source for persisted config.** New persisted fields go through `persisted_session_payload` in [cleave/config_schema.py](cleave/config_schema.py) so load, save, and dirty tracking stay aligned; do not add a parallel serializer.
- **Dirty tracking is computed, not marked.** Mutate session state and let the signature compare detect changes; never reintroduce `mark_config_dirty()`. See [cleave/config_snapshot.py](cleave/config_snapshot.py) (`persisted_session_signature`).
- **Thin controllers, split by feature.** [cleave/viz/controls.py](cleave/viz/controls.py) `TuningControls` coordinates focus and input and delegates to [cleave/viz/config_save.py](cleave/viz/config_save.py), [cleave/viz/preset_curation_controls.py](cleave/viz/preset_curation_controls.py), [cleave/viz/render_overlay_controls.py](cleave/viz/render_overlay_controls.py), [cleave/viz/render_post_fx_controls.py](cleave/viz/render_post_fx_controls.py); do not let one class accumulate unrelated responsibilities.
- **Model, controller, and view separate.** Session dataclasses in [cleave/viz/session.py](cleave/viz/session.py); view model via `TuningViewStateBuilder` in [cleave/viz/tuning_view_state.py](cleave/viz/tuning_view_state.py); [cleave/viz/tuning_panel_draw.py](cleave/viz/tuning_panel_draw.py) draws the live tuning panel.
- **Readiness enforced with types.** Prefer `VisualizerSeed`, `VisualizerCore`, `LiveVisualizerRuntime`, and `RenderVisualizerRuntime` in [cleave/viz/app.py](cleave/viz/app.py) over optional fields guarded by `assert ... is not None`. Core composes seed via `runtime.seed.*`.
- **Typed dependency injection.** Pass [cleave/viz/focus_context.py](cleave/viz/focus_context.py) `FocusContext` (or similar small typed context), never a dict of lambdas or `setattr` by string.
- **Public APIs across modules.** No cross-module underscore imports; expose helpers on a class or module if another package needs them.
- **One default per setting.** Parse defaults and fallbacks live in [cleave/config_schema.py](cleave/config_schema.py), not duplicated in load, save, or session helpers.
- **Descriptor-driven config sections.** `editor`, `render.post_fx`, and `render.overlay` use field and section descriptors in [cleave/config_schema.py](cleave/config_schema.py). `layers` and `timeline` use bespoke parse and persist (nested per-stem layers; per-slot `timeline.lanes` with baseline and `SlotCue` lists); defaults stay single-sourced from constants in that module.
- **Registry-driven effect dispatch.** Adding an effect means a registry entry plus one effect module using [cleave/effects/handlers.py](cleave/effects/handlers.py); do not add per-effect branches in [cleave/effects/runtime.py](cleave/effects/runtime.py).
- **Panel field manifest.** New tuning panel rows register `RowFieldDef` in [cleave/viz/row_fields.py](cleave/viz/row_fields.py) (`panel_label`, `format_value`, `apply_horizontal`, `present_style`); tree chrome from `row_tree_indent_depth` in [cleave/viz/row_sections.py](cleave/viz/row_sections.py). Do not add per-`RowKind` label or mutation branches in [cleave/viz/tuning_panel_draw.py](cleave/viz/tuning_panel_draw.py) or [cleave/viz/controls.py](cleave/viz/controls.py). **Conditional rows and expandable children** are baked into `RowLayout` at build time; any session field that gates row presence must appear in `view_state_structure_signature()` ([cleave/viz/tuning_view_state.py](cleave/viz/tuning_view_state.py)) so the layout rebuilds when it changes.
- **Shared frame finish.** Live and offline paths call [cleave/viz/frame_finish.py](cleave/viz/frame_finish.py); do not duplicate fade, overlay composite, or present logic.
- **Render section `enabled` gates runtime.** Child effects under `render.post_fx` and `render.overlay` must respect the parent header `enabled` flag in the frame path (not only panel dimming). Post-FX helpers live in [cleave/viz/post_fx.py](cleave/viz/post_fx.py); GPU pitfalls in [.cursor/rules/gl-post-process.mdc](.cursor/rules/gl-post-process.mdc).

## Larger features

When a change is more than a small localized edit (new feature, config or effect type, overlay section, or anything touching several modules), consider the architecture first. Refactor or introduce an abstraction when it keeps the change cohesive rather than bolting onto an existing class. Read [docs/architecture-refactor.md](docs/architecture-refactor.md) and this rule before expanding scope.
